mic echoes.

The methodical thumping is contrasted against the
naturally soothing sound of waves from “Splash.”

The looping black and white video “Splash” shows
the choppy waves of a lake that are only interrupted by
the sudden splash of a person.

“House” is Jones’ only work without a soundtrack.
A large red house rests on a metal rocker that mechani-
cally pushes it side to side. ‘=

